==English==
===Etymology===
From Old French ''[[molture]]'' (modern ''[[mouture]]''), from mediaeval Latin ''[[molitura]]'', from the past participle stem of ''[[molere]]'' ‘grind’.  Compare ''[[mill]]''.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈmʌlʧə/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{italbrac|Scots and Historic}} A [[toll]] paid to a miller, mill-owner etc. for grinding corn.

